  "text": "Substantial differences in BDNF levels (normalized to β-actin levels) were observed across treatment groups in both the frontal cortex (F [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] = 0.5364, p = 0.71) and hippocampus (F [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] = 4.721, p = 0.011), as is shown in Figure 6 . Ovariectomy reduced BDNF levels in the hippocampus (p = 0,0085 Tukey's HSD). Ghrelin normalized BDNF levels in the hippocampus (p = 0.012 vs. ovariectomized alone, Tukey's HSD) and this effect was not reversed by tamoxifen. Tamoxifen alone increases BDNF levels in the hippocampus (p = 0.0068 Tukey's HSD).",
